FOOT & MOUTH DISEASE - PARAGUAY
*******************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Mon, 14 Jul 2003
From: Matias SACLA <msacla@yahoo.com>
Source: Campo Grande News, Brasil, 12 Jul 2003 [translated and edited]
<http://www.campograndenews.com/view.htm?id=184456>

Government of Paraguay confirms outbreak of foot and mouth disease
------------------------------------------------------------------
The president of Senacsa (National Animal Health Service) of Paraguay,
Gerardo Bogado, confirmed the confirmation, today, of a focus of foot and
mouth disease (FMD) in Pozo Hondo, region of Boqron (700 km from Assunsion)
-- on the border with Argentina and Bolivia. As announced by Bogado,
preventive measures have been undertaken by the immediate slaughter of 95
animals, following positive laboratory results in 13 of 17 tests conducted.
The minister of agriculture, Dario Baungarten, confirmed that the
government was aggressively implementing the National Sanitary Emergency in
order to control the disease outbreak.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The press item does not specify the species involved. We assume that it
relates to cattle. The following chronology is derived from a later
notification by the Paraguayan authorities, kindly forwarded by Dr Matias
Sacla:
8 Jul 2003: first notification obtained by SENASCA from an Indian
settlement in Pozo Hondo, Boqueron , 3 km from the border with Argentina
and 7 km from the Bolivian border. A sample taken and sent to the central
laboratory.
9 Jul 2003: 17 blood samples and epithelium sampled; banning of animal
movements.
10 Jul 2003: neighbouring countries notified on suspected FMD outbreak.
11 Jul 2003: The central laboratory notifies that 15 of the 17 samples has
been found positive (enzyme linked immunosorbent assay).
The central laboratory reports the identification of FMD serotypes O and A.
The said notification is a preliminary one. Additional data will be sent
when available. - Mod.AS]
